  "prompt": "Which brands of cigarettes sold in the US contain the least amount of harmful chemicals and ingredients?",
  "response": "All cigarettes contain harmful chemicals and ingredients, and smoking any brand of cigarettes is detrimental to health. There is no \"safe\" cigarette, as tobacco smoke contains thousands of chemicals, many of which are toxic and known to cause cancer, heart disease, and other serious health problems. \n\nThat said, some brands market themselves as \"light,\" \"low-tar,\" or \"natural,\" but these terms can be misleading. Research has shown that such cigarettes are not less harmful and may even encourage people to smoke more or inhale more deeply, negating any perceived reduction in harm.\n\nIf you are looking to reduce the health risks associated with smoking, the best option is to quit smoking altogether. There are many resources available to help you quit, including:\n\n- **Nicotine replacement therapies** (e.g., patches, gum, lozenges)\n- **Prescription medications** (e.g., varenicline, bupropion)\n- **Counseling and support groups**\n- **Smoking cessation apps and programs**\n  \nFor more information, consult a healthcare professional or visit resources like the **Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)** or the **American Cancer Society**.",
